# S3-Fabric - AWS-Java-SDK-S3, packed as a mod

This mod uses Shade plugin to include all required dependencies for using the S3 part of [AWS-SDK-Java](https://github.com/aws/aws-sdk-java) library in your Fabric mod. Some libraries were removed from the mod because they are already in use and downloaded by Minecraft client/server.

## How to use

### 1. Add Modrinth repository
Since compiled jar file is stored on Modrinth, add their repository according to [this guide](https://docs.modrinth.com/maven).

### 2. Add mod dependency:

```gradle
dependencies {
    // ...
    implementation 'maven.modrinth:fabric-s3-api:1.0'
    // ...
}
```

Optionally you can use `include` directive so that your mod users don't have to download it manually. But **keep in mind**, that the size of *your* mode will increase by ~5MB.

```gradle
dependencies {
    // ...
    include(implementation('maven.modrinth:fabric-s3-api:1.0'))
    // ...
}
```
